Package: citefrag
Type: Package
Title: Measuring Fragmentation in Longitudinal Citation Networks
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Zarina",
           family = "Vakhitova",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "zarina.vakhitova@deakin.edu.au",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-2853-7968"))
Description: Tools for measuring within-group versus between-group citation 
    preference in longitudinal journal panels. Provides the pair-averaged 
    within-cluster to between-cluster citation ratio under several 
    normalisations, exact and Monte Carlo permutation tests of statistical 
    significance, directional asymmetry analysis between traditions, 
    alternative-specification and fixed-subpanel robustness checks, and 
    piecewise regression with bootstrap confidence intervals for locating 
    structural breaks in ratio trajectories. Developed to accompany 
    Vakhitova (2026) on the fragmentation of criminology; the machinery 
    is general to any longitudinal node-by-node exchange network with 
    a priori group labels.
